<HEAD>Foreign Minister Leaves for Treatment at Mayo Clinic</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DUBLIN, Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Irish Foriegn Minister Brian Lenihan, who
has a serious blood disorder, left Wednesday to undergo treatment
at the renowned Mayo Clinic in Rochester, Minn.
   Lenihan, 58, who is also the deputy prime minister, flew from
Dublin Airport in a private jet accompanied by a medical team.
   Prime Minister Charles Haughey has taken over Lenihan's foreign
affairs portfolio temporarily.
   Lenihan, who has been ill for more than six months, is suffering
from haemocromatosis, a blood disease that attacks the liver and
can also cause diabetes.
</TEXT>
